@flexiarg vsatelier/session-as-rehearsal
@title Session as Rehearsal
@audience facilitators, cooperative learning practitioners, workshop designers
@tone analytic
@style design-pattern
@sigils [🎭/排]
@references [vsatlas/facilitation-scaffolds vsatlas/cooperative-learning-environment vsatelier/cluster-as-agenda]

! conclusion:
  Treat each facilitated session with the constellation as a rehearsal —
  a bounded, low-stakes space where participants practice the skills of
  collective interpretation, deliberation, and commitment before applying
  them to consequential decisions.

  + context: You are introducing deliberation practices to groups that have not previously done collective sense-making. This does not apply to experienced deliberation teams who need no scaffolding.
  + IF:
    Participants are new to interpreting linked stories and producing
    shared decisions from spatial patterns.

  + HOWEVER:
    Jumping straight to consequential decisions in an unfamiliar medium
    risks poor outcomes and eroded trust.

  + THEN:
    Structure early sessions as rehearsals: use a small anthology, set
    a low-stakes question, walk through the full cycle (explore the
    constellation → flag a pattern → discuss → decide → record the
    decision). Debrief the process itself, not just the content. Graduate
    to consequential sessions once the group has practised the cycle.

  + BECAUSE:
    An atelier is a place of practice before it is a place of production.
    The deliberation skills — reading space, articulating patterns,
    translating observations into commitments — are learned through
    doing, not through instruction. Rehearsal lowers the cost of error
    and builds the group's confidence in its own capacity.

  + STATUS:
    status[sketch]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Design a 90-minute rehearsal session plan using a 3-story anthology.]
    next[Define the debrief questions that distinguish process learning from content learning.]
    next[Test whether groups that rehearse produce better-provenance decisions than groups that do not.]
